+    Top level `val` properties and `const val` properties have to be written in screaming snake notation. Local `val` and `const val` are written in lower camel case. Properties with a mutable type (e.g. `MutableList`, `MutableMap`, `ArrayList`, etc.) are not considered to be constants even when declared as `val` because their contents can be modified.
 
